Generally ignoring *all* errors is a mistake -- in this case, it's hiding the fact that you're calling a nonexistent `hookLastFiresDeleted` method.  If there's a specific kind of error you're looking for, you can do something like
```js
} catch (err) {
  if (err.code == 'whatever') {
    // handle it
  } else {
    throw err;
  }
}
```
that way anything unexpected still gets thrown.

